Waste Management Inc said itsent a letter to the ChemLawn Corp board, saying it is preparedto increase its bid for ChemLawn to 33 dlrs a share,from 27 dlrs, if ChemLawn promptly negotiates and executes asimple two-step merger agreement containing only essentialcovenants and conditions.    Upon such an agreement, Waste Management said, it wouldamend its 27 dlrs a share cash tender offer. Reuter&#3;